            <h2>Easy to use</h2>
            <p>Cassette's <code>Assets</code> helper works in view pages, layouts and partials.</p>
            <p>Reference the scripts you directly require.</p>
            <p>Tell Cassette where to render the <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tags.</p>
            <p class="minor"><a href="@Url.DocumentationUrl("stylesheets")">Stylesheets</a> and <a href="@Url.RouteUrl("Documentation", new{path="html-templates"})">HTML Templates</a> are also supported</p>
        </div>
        <div class="file">
            <pre><code><span class="code-tag">@@{</span>
  <span class="code-type">Assets</span>.Scripts.Reference(<span class="string">"Scripts/app/page.js"</span>);
<span class="code-tag">}</span>
